billion of New Secured Notes; provided that such cash payment is 
funded by debt on terms that, taken as a whole, are no less favorable 
to Dynegy than the terms of the New Secured Notes (except that the 
interest rate of such debt may be up to 12% per annum and there 
shall be no restrictions as to the maturity date of such debt). 

